# Code Accuracy — Safety Critical

This codebase is used for **structural engineering**. Incorrect code can lead to unsafe designs. Treat every calculation as safety-critical.

- **Stay extremely close to the source material** (code standards, reference equations, textbook derivations). Do not improvise formulas or invent approximations.
- **If there is any ambiguity** — in a spec, equation, sign convention, unit, load combination, boundary condition, or code clause — **stop and ask the user before generating code.** Do not guess.
- When implementing a code provision (ACI 318, AISC 360, etc.), cite the exact clause number in a comment.
- Double-check unit consistency (kip vs lb, in vs ft, psi vs ksi, etc.) at every interface boundary.
